column1:
Values for state Medicaid beneficiaries (Column BK) were missing for some states in some years due to missing data in the Medicaid report.  Data was gathered to fill these missing values.  The data were gathered from the following:
     CA 2014 http://www.dhcs.ca.gov/dataandstats/reports/Documents/MMCD_Enrollment_Reports/MMCDEnrollRptJune2014.pdf
     CA 2015 http://www.dhcs.ca.gov/dataandstats/reports/Documents/MMCD_Enrollment_Reports/MMCEnrollRptJune2015.pdf
     CO 2014 https://www.colorado.gov/pacific/sites/default/files/Medicaid%20Member%20Caseload%20Monthly%20Report%20June%202014%20by%20Age%20Group.pdf
     CO 2015 https://www.colorado.gov/pacific/sites/default/files/Medicaid%20Member%20Caseload%20by%20County%20-%20By%20Age%20Groups%20June%202015.pdf
     NJ 2015 http://www.state.nj.us/humanservices/dmahs/news/reports/enrollment_2015.pdf
     ND 2014 https://www.medicaid.gov/medicaid/program-information/downloads/updated-july-enrollment-data.pdf
     ND 2015 https://www.medicaid.gov/medicaid/program-information/downloads/updated-july-2015-enrollment-data.pdf

Population, employment, unemployment, unemployment rate, and personal income have all been updated going back to 1980 in light of updates made by the Census and BLS.

EITC parameters for 3 or more dependents have been added.

Low income uninsured children and its respective percent have been changed from a 3 year moving average to single-year observations.
